The good billboard: two pieces of information, white on black, yellow accent for the URL. A driver at 60 mph reads this in full.

## Quick Exercise

Print a sign and walk away. At 3m, 6m, 10m—when does the text become unreadable? That's your legibility limit. Now think about your actual viewing distance.

## Quick Recap

- Signage follows an inverse of normal UI design: less information is always better.
- 7 words maximum for highway billboards. One call to action.
- Heavy/black weight fonts only. Regular weight disappears at distance.
- Test by simulating actual viewing distance before finalizing.
- Distance rule: 1 inch letter height ≈ 100 feet readable distance.